Step 1: Make main.py Functions Callable
In main.py, wrap your logic inside a function:

# main.py
def run_pcat_processing(pcat_dir, classifier_file, access_dir, output_dir):
    # Your actual logic here
    print(f"PCAT Dir: {pcat_dir}")
    print(f"Classifier File: {classifier_file}")
    print(f"Access Review Dir: {access_dir}")
    print(f"Output Dir: {output_dir}")

    # Simulate processing...
    return "Processing completed successfully."
Make sure main.py does not run anything directly on script start (i.e., no code under if __name__ == "__main__" unless needed).


Step 2: Import main.py in ui.py
At the top of ui.py, import the function:


from main import run_pcat_processing


 Call It in Your GUI's on_process() Method
Inside your PCATRoleClassifierPanel class in ui.py, update on_process:


def on_process(self, event):
    try:
        # Get inputs from GUI
        pcat_dir = self.pcat_extracts.get_value()
        classifier_file = self.excel_file.get_value()
        access_dir = self.myaccess_review.get_value()
        output_dir = self.output_file.get_value()

        # Validate inputs (optional)
        if not all([pcat_dir, classifier_file, access_dir, output_dir]):
            self.output_display.SetLabel("Please fill in all fields.")
            return

        # Call processing logic
        result = run_pcat_processing(pcat_dir, classifier_file, access_dir, output_dir)

        # Show result in UI
        self.output_display.SetLabel(result)
    except Exception as e:
        self.output_display.SetLabel(f" Error: {str(e)}")



When the user selects all folders/files and clicks Process, it will:

Call your main.py logic,

Pass all the values,

Display the result in the GUI.

